, \"from\": 424, \"to\": 440}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympic Games\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 468}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 492}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was included in the Olympics in Tokyo in 2021, but as part of the climbing event together with lead climbing and bouldering.\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 550, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.985422521964296, \"rank\": 0.014656176304941012, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 546}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 576}, {\"ngram\": \"the climbing event\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"lead climbing\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 626}, {\"ngram\": \"bouldering\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 641}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time there will be two climbing events, speed and combined, in Paris.\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 711, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999906157659, \"rank\": 9.384240469999042e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two climbing events\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The current world records for speed climbing are 6.24 seconds for women and 4.9 seconds for men, both much faster than the performances of gold medalists in Tokyo because speed climbers do not do well enough in comprehensive competitions.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for